      • isComponentValidationSupported

        public boolean isComponentValidationSupported(Component component)
        Determine if this validator instance can be used with the given component. Returns true for Field. Override to return true for other classes and override getComponentValue(Component) to support the component.
        Parameters:
        component - The component.
        Returns:
        true if this validator supports the given component, false otherwise.

      • isValidValue

        protected abstract boolean isValidValue(String valueStr)
        Check if the value is valid, the isValueRequired property will have already been validated against an empty value. A null or empty string will never be passed to this method.
        Parameters:
        valueStr - The value as returned by getComponentValue() .
        Returns:
        true if the component data is valid.

      • isValueRequired

        public boolean isValueRequired()
        Get if a value is required. If false then no entry is always considered valid.
        Returns:
        true if a value is required, false otherwise.

      • setValueRequired

        public void setValueRequired(boolean isValueRequired)
        Set if a value is required. If false then no entry is always considered valid.
